{"id": "duc04-testb-15:19#58", "contents": "Levin's research has shown that homosexuals are disproportionately affected by violent crime, with roughly half of their attackers being young males aged 22 or younger. He noted that hate crimes are unique in that the violence itself is often the primary goal, rather than a means to an end. Levin also highlighted the social stigma faced by the LGBTQ+ community, stating that their perceived \"social stature\" makes them vulnerable to being viewed as \"appropriate targets\" for violence."}
